cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

The paper proposes a new technique for neural machine translation (NMT) that improves the quality of translations across multiple domains. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and machine translation. The paper also uses neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed technique, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the technique on English-to-French translation, which could also place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as machine translation is a subfield of computer vision.
